-- Stocks Advance as Mining Companies Stage Rally; Xstrata, Rio Tinto Advance
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2010-10-20T11:03:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/stocks-advance-as-mining-companies-stage-rally-xstrata-rio-tinto-advance.html
U.K. stocks advanced, rebounding
from earlier losses, as mining companies climbed.  The benchmark FTSE 100 gained 0.4 percent to 5,723.89 at 12
p.m. in London. The gauge earlier fell as much as 0.4 percent.  Xstrata Plc, Anglo American Plc and Rio Tinto Group all
rose at least 2 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  